# Tech stack & data authority

**Evolving snapshot** while finishing control-plane foundations/capabilities. Update when stack roles change. Do not invent new stores without a spec/ticket. Local wiring: `README.md` / `.env.example`.

| System | Used for | Authority |
|--------|----------|-----------|
| **FastAPI + Socket.IO** | HTTP API, startup migrations, realtime transport | Entry/transport only |
| **uv / Python 3.12** | Project env, `uv run`, lockfile | Standard invoke path |
| **Postgres (application)** | Run lifecycle, commands, transitions, budgets, outbox, cursors, authz projections, linked-run rollups, durable approvals | **Authoritative** control-plane transactional state (local port `55432`) |
| **Postgres (Temporal)** | Temporal persistence only | Separate DB — **not** domain authority |
| **Redis** | Fan-out / notifications for realtime + approval wakes | **Not** durable authority; durable events stay in application Postgres |
| **Supabase** | Hosted Postgres path + vector for memory-related retrieval | Memory/vector when wired; do not confuse with Temporal or app control DB |
| **MongoDB + Beanie** | Immutable definitions, Effective Run Config, operation bindings, workspace/artifact metadata, workflow-shaped docs | **Authoritative** for those document payloads (`AsyncMongoClient`, DB `belllabsbiotech`) |
| **Temporal** | Durable workflows/activities, retries, sandbox-bound agent work | Execution mechanics only |
| **Neo4j** | Approved canonical graph knowledge | Graph authority; preflight/refinement read-only unless a later spec says otherwise |
| **Object storage (S3/aioboto3)** | Large immutable payloads, artifacts, reports, snapshots | Blob authority (Mongo holds refs/metadata) |
| **OpenAI Agents SDK + Docker** | Governed agent runs, tools, sandboxed exec, Temporal durable-workflow plugin | Bound through ports/bindings; never invents control-plane state by existing |

## Hard rules

- Temporal, Redis, Socket.IO, and model output must **not** be the system of record for run lifecycle, budgets, or admissions.
- Prompts, skills, MCP tools, plugins, memory packs, and agent output are **never** authority merely because they exist (catalog + exact bindings required where specs say so).
- When unsure where state lives, check the matching `F*`/`C*` spec in `../biotech-meta/docs/specs/pre-research/` before coding.
